---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Aminu Abdusalam" description="A bit about me.">
  <section class="container container-narrow prose">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      I'm a Product Manager 2 at Microsoft on Consumer Commerce, an engineer, and a
      builder who can't stop tinkering.
    </p>

    <p>
      I grew up in Nigeria and moved to the U.S. for college at <strong>Fisk University</strong>
      in Nashville, where I studied Computer Science on the W.E.B. Du Bois Honors track,
      graduated as <strong>valedictorian</strong> with a 4.0, and helped Fisk win the <a
      href="https://www.nfl.com/news/nfl-hbcu-battle-of-the-brains-competition-fisk-university"
      target="_blank" rel="noopener">NFL Battle of the Brains</a> championship.
    </p>

    <p>
      I started at Microsoft as a Program Manager intern on Xbox Game Pass while still in
      school. After graduating in 2023, I joined full-time on Consumer Commerce and have
      been shipping commerce experiences ever since. That list includes the introduction of
      Xbox Game Pass Standard (now Premium), Fortnite Crew inside Xbox Game Pass Ultimate,
      Ask-a-Parent for kids requesting subscriptions, Xbox mobile app store capabilities,
      the Recurring Discounts capability, and region-based fraud remediation. Three
      promotions in under three years (L59 → L62), which mostly means I've learned to ship things
      and write clearly.
    </p>

    <h2>Timeline</h2>
    <ul class="timeline">
      <li>
        <span class="year">2025</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Product Manager 2, Microsoft</strong>
          <p>Consumer Commerce. Broader ownership across subscription, purchase, and fraud surfaces. Also building internal Copilot CLI plugins for the org.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="year">2023</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Product Manager, Microsoft</strong>
          <p>Joined Consumer Commerce full-time (June 2023 to Feb 2025). First shipped experiences for hundreds of millions of Xbox players.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="year">2023</span>
        <div>
          <strong>B.S. Computer Science, Fisk University</strong>
          <p>Honors track (W.E.B. Du Bois). 4.0 GPA. NFL Battle of the Brains champion. Nashville, TN.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="year">2022</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Program Manager Intern, Microsoft</strong>
          <p>Interned on Xbox Game Pass. Shipped a feature for the business to modify existing products and measure business performance.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="year">2021</span>
        <div>
          <strong>SWE + PM Intern, Microsoft</strong>
          <p>Built anomaly detection models on top of Kusto and Geneva to catch subscription-metric regressions before they hit customers.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="year">2020</span>
        <div>
          <strong>IT Intern, Froedtert Health</strong>
          <p>Managed multi-site IT for 20,000+ endpoints across 20 locations. Learned how enterprise IT actually holds together.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Honors, wins, and things I'm proud of</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>3 promotions in under 3 years at Microsoft</strong> — moved from PM 1 to PM 2 faster than the standard clock.</li>
      <li><strong>Valedictorian, Fisk University</strong> — Class of 2023. 4.0 GPA, W.E.B. Du Bois Honors track.</li>
      <li><strong>NFL Battle of the Brains</strong> — Champion (Fisk team). $85K prize + NFL Draft experience.</li>
      <li><strong>Erastus Milo Cravath Presidential Scholarship</strong> — Full-ride to Fisk ($128K).</li>
      <li><strong>Oracle NetSuite Case Competition</strong> — 1st place.</li>
      <li><strong>Microsoft PM HBCU Hack</strong> — 3rd place.</li>
      <li><strong>BE-Smart Hack</strong> — HP & Nvidia Awards.</li>
      <li><strong>Summit Partners Case Competition</strong> — 3rd place.</li>
      <li><strong>McKinsey Diversity Leadership Scholar</strong>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What I'm into</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Subscription and marketplace commerce (payments, entitlements, tax, fraud)</li>
      <li>AI agents that actually change how PMs work day-to-day</li>
      <li>Spending time with people I care about</li>
      <li>Soccer, bouldering, pickleball, paddleboarding</li>
      <li>Mentoring students breaking into tech — I was the CS Club President and a TA at Fisk, and I still find time for it</li>
      <li>Writing about the messy in-between of product and engineering</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="cta-line">
      <a href="mailto:aminuabdusalam2019@gmail.com">Say hi →</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose {
    padding-block: var(--space-10) var(--space-8);
  }
  .prose h1 {
    font-size: var(--fs-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }
  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--fs-xl);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  .prose h2::before {
    content: '## ';
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
  }
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .prose .lead {
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
    color: var(--color-text-strong);
  }
  .prose ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
  }
  .timeline {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    border-left: 1px solid var(--color-border-strong);
    margin-left: var(--space-2);
  }
  .timeline li {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    padding: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
    position: relative;
  }
  .timeline li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: -5px;
    top: var(--space-6);
    width: 9px;
    height: 9px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 12px var(--color-accent-glow);
  }
  .year {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    min-width: 60px;
    padding-top: 4px;
  }
  .timeline strong {
    color: var(--color-text-strong);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }
  .timeline p {
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .cta-line {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
</style>
